  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Term neonates less than 28 days of age at enrollment, referred to healthcare professionals
        due to suspected C Difficile Associated Disease (CDAD).
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Subject is suffering from diarrhea or other signs or symptoms consistent with CDAD (as
             described in section 5.2.3)

          -  Presence of either toxin A or B (or both) of C. difficile in the stool within 24 hours
             prior to enrollment using the C. difficile Quik Chek CompleteÂ® diagnostic test,
             provided by the sponsor

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Subject will be excluded from participation if any of the following apply:

          -  Preterm neonates

          -  Negative C. difficile toxin test
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
